                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100118">Närke</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1535" notBefore="1470">15th century, last quarter to 16th century, first half</origDate>. The most recent research on the text argues that it was written in the diocese of <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100375">Kräcklinge</placeName> in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100118">Närke</placeName> between ca 1470 and 1535, cf <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107590">Klingneus (1981)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="98" to="100" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. The manuscript is presumed to have belonged to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>. The manuscript was put on display in the exhibition room (<quote>visningssalen</quote>) at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National LIbrary</orgName> from <date when="1878"/>.</p>
                        </provenance>
